parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition coil fuse can cause the vehicle to stall or fail to start, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or fails to start
the ignition coil fuse blows repeatedly
the vehicle experiences intermittent stalling or hesitation.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to stall or fail to start, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or fails to start
the dashboard gauges (speedometer
odometer
tachometer
gas gauge
temperature gauge) malfunction or stop working
the vehicle experiences intermittent stalling or hesitation.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch hydraulic system can cause the clutch pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The illumination of the air bag light can indicate a faulty air bag system, which can lead to accidents or injuries in the event of a crash.
symptoms: The air bag light illuminates on the dashboard
the vehicle experiences intermittent stalling or hesitation.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbags to deploy in a crash can lead to serious injuries or fatalities, as the occupants are not protected from the impact.
symptoms: Airbags do not deploy in a crash
despite the severity of the impact
resulting in injuries or fatalities.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Inaccurate or Faulty Mass Air Flow Sensor
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A faulty Mass Air Flow sensor can cause the "Service Engine Soon" light to come on, leading to unnecessary repairs and potentially causing the engine to malfunction.
symptoms: The "Service Engine Soon" light comes on
and the dealer diagnoses a faulty Mass Air Flow sensor
resulting in unnecessary repairs.
